				\begin{document}$${{{\mathrm{DQE}}}}\left( \nu \right) = {{{\mathrm{DQE}}}}\left( {\nu = 0,D = 5\,\mu {{{\mathrm{Gy}}}}_{\mathrm{air}}} \right) \times \frac{{{{{\mathrm{MTF}}}}^2\left( \nu \right)}}{{{{{\mathrm{NTF}}}}\left( \nu \right)}},$$\end{document}where DQE(ν = 0, D = 5 µGyair) = 87% is obtained according to the derived model, and NTF(ν) is the noise transfer function, which, for the photon-counting detector, is assumed46 to be independent of spatial frequency and equal to 1.
